NAME
    `IO::Async::Loop::Event' - use `IO::Async' with `Event'

SYNOPSIS
     use IO::Async::Loop::Event;

     my $loop = IO::Async::Loop::Event->new();

     $loop->add( ... );

     $loop->run;

DESCRIPTION
    This subclass of IO::Async::Loop uses Event to perform its work.

AUTHOR
    Paul Evans <leonerd@leonerd.org.uk>

